  "explanation": "The defendant, a first-time offender with no prior criminal record, embezzled $25,000 to pay off personal debts. Mitigating factors include the lack of prior criminal history and the fact that the defendant has already made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and an attempt to rectify the harm caused. The spectator's outburst in the courtroom has no bearing on the legal determination of the sentence. Balancing the seriousness of the economic crime with the defendant's clean record and proactive repayment, a sentence of 6 months of incarceration is appropriate, followed by supervised release and a mandate to pay the remaining restitution.",
